cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with text generation tasks. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method to improve the performance of neural models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of reinforcement learning. The use of denoising auto-encoder (DAE) also suggests that it could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as text generation is a common task in image captioning.
